<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,258,787]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,451,690,715]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">General distribution.</emphasis>
This is an eastern species distributed from southeastern 
<collectingCountry box="[1094,1178,690,714]" name="Canada" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Canada</collectingCountry>
to Florida and west to Missouri, Oklahoma, and Texas.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,258,787]" box="[197,1264,762,787]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,352,763,787]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Larval hosts.</emphasis>
Larvae have been reported feeding on a species of bracket fungus (
<bibRefCitation author="Covell" box="[1108,1252,762,786]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" refString="Covell, C. V., Jr. (1984) A field guide to the moths of eastern North America. Houghton Mifflin Co.: Boston, 496 pp." type="book" year="1984">
Covell 
<number box="[1191,1252,762,786]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="1984.0">1984</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
